FeedPackage.Title: Manatee.Trello

FeedPackage.Description: A fully object-oriented .Net wrapper for the TrelloAPI.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
A lot has changed with this release. Your code WILL break. Please be sure to read the wiki pages at https://bitbucket.org/gregsdennis/manatee.trello/wiki/Home.
See Trello board for this project at https://trello.com/#board/manatee-trello-net/5144051cbd0da6681200201e. Feedback and questions are welcome through the board, on StackOverflow, or by emailing littlecrabsolutions@yahoo.com.
Extracted JSON and REST providers into separate assemblies and published them individually on Nuget. New request queuing engine provides better support for "Store and Forward" feature. Monitors network connectivity automatically. Updated logging to be more concise. Moved request processing to a background thread. No longer prevents application from closing smoothly. Actions and Notifications now possess all properties. There are no more subclasses. Moved to a better underlying architecture, keeping in mind the SOLID principles.

FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
WARNING: This release contains many breaking changes, but is remarkably faster than v0.6.9. The previous versions will remain available for some time. Please be sure to read the wiki pages at https://bitbucket.org/gregsdennis/manatee.trello/wiki/Home.
See Trello board for this project at https://trello.com/b/BVlClkAR/. Feedback and questions are welcome through the board, on StackOverflow, or by emailing littlecrabsolutions@yahoo.com.
v1.0 Refactored to include a new synchronization framework supporting all entities. Removed TrelloService in favor of direct object instantiation. Drastically reduced call frequency by: - utilizing all of the data received from the API, - consolidating multiple updates into a single call after a configurable idle time, and - sending only data changes, not entire objects. Exposed collection properties as specific collection classes to allow direct modification. Changes are tracked so that incoming updates do not overwrite unsubmitted changes. Caching is more reliable. All objects now expose an Updated event.

FeedPackage.Description: RequestReduce allows any IIS based website to automaticaly sprite background images into a single optimized PNG as well as combine and minify CSS and Javascript with absolutely no coding beyond a few config tweaks. RequestReduce excercises common best practices when serving its javascript, css and sprited images ensuring that the appropriate caching headers are sent to the browser so that browsers will not need to pull down a new http response until absolutely necessary. Chances are you will see an immediate rise in your yslow and google page speed tests.
FeedPackage.Summary: RequestReduce is a .Net Library and HttpModule providing automatic CSS background image optimization and spriting as well as CSS and Javascript merging and minification.
FeedPackage.Tags: CSS Minification Sprites Website Performance Optimization Compression Minify Javascript
